e"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EBell\u0027s palsy typically involves \u003Cstrong\u003Eall five branches\u003C/strong\u003E of the facial nerve on the affected side. These branches are the temporal, zygomatic, buccal, mandibular, and cervical branches. The condition results in paralysis or weakness of the muscles of facial expression on one side of the face.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Bell\u0027s palsy is a condition that affects the facial nerve (cranial nerve VII), leading to unilateral facial paralysis.","The facial nerve has five main branches: temporal, zygomatic, buccal, mandibular, and cervical.","Bell\u0027s palsy typically involves all five branches of the facial nerve on the affected side."],"references":["Singh, V. (2023). Textbook of Anatomy-Head, Neck and Brain, Volume III-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Patestas, M. A., \u0026 Gartner, L. P. (2016). A textbook of neuroanatomy. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Patel, C. R., Fernandez-Miranda, J. C., Wang, W. H., \u0026 Wang, E. W. (2016). Skull Base Anatomy. Otolaryngologic clinics of North America, 49(1), 9\u201320. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.otc.2015.09.001","Anderson, B. W., Kortz, M. W., Black, A. C., \u0026 Al Kharazi, K. A. (2023). Anatomy, Head and Neck, Skull. In StatPearls. StatPearls Publishing"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58749"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17972"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21353"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21353","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21353"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/mFwaTBNSCJPoh6bQeqtQHKJl6tXppp.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/mFwaTBNSCJPoh6bQeqtQHKJl6tXppp.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":392,"height":600}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58749","links":{"self":"https://app.e